Wabby - Create semi-random sentences based upon a body of text.
===============================================================

This module is used to create semi-random sentences based on a body of text.
It uses a markov-like method of storing probabilities of word transitions.
It is good for annoying people on IRC, AIM, or other such fun mediums.

See perldoc Silly::Wabby for code examples and a longer description.

Wabby was implemented by Nathan Poznick <kraken@wang-fu.org>.  Send comments,
suggestions, bug reports, or anything else to him.

This code is distributed under the GPLv2.  See COPYING for details.
